          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Papert's Principle</td><td class="text-gray-400">Mental growth depends not on acquiring new skills, but on acquiring new ways to use existing knowledge.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Exception Principle</td><td class="text-gray-400">Easier to extend old frames by adding exceptions than to replace them.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Recursion Principle</td><td class="text-gray-400">The same strategies apply at every level of decomposition.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Predestined Learning</td><td class="text-gray-400">Sufficient innate constraint makes certain learning outcomes nearly inevitable.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
